
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-srose-smimelock-00.txt'>
    <title>"Using Secure DNS to Assert S/MIME Usage", Scott Rose</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-srose-smimelock-00.txt</link>
    <description>This draft defines and discusses the use of a new DNS resource record (RR) type to address S/MIME downgrade attacks.  The SMIMELOCK RR allows a domain to convey general message security policy. Primarily, this RR allows the domain owner to advertise a policy that all legitimate messages from this domain will be signed by a verifiable certificate.</description>
    <dc:date>2013-09-22T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
